# {{pathology}} Crohn's regional [[enteritis]] is a sometimes [[chronic]] [[inflammatory]] [[disease]], i.e, an [[inflammatory bowel disease]] that can involve any part of the [[digestive tract]], from the [[mouth]] to the [[anus]], which can present as the worst [[stomach ache]] of your life, sending you trotting into the [[emergency room]] and being subsequently operated and rapidly having one's [[viscera]] delivered onto one's abdomen (one has seen the Polaroids of one's self so [[eviscerated]]).

